responded: The patch modifies the method `doToQuery` in `SpanTermQueryBuilder.java` to handle unmapped fields by returning a `MatchNoDocsQuery` instead of a `SpanTermQuery` with a term that won't match anything.

From the older version code (ref 309d234bf08d9361c987411146acc0003cb511fc), the `doToQuery` method is simpler:
```java
@Override
protected SpanQuery doToQuery(SearchExecutionContext context) throws IOException {
    MappedFieldType mapper = context.getFieldType(fieldName);
    Term term;
    if (mapper == null) {
        term = new Term(fieldName, BytesRefs.toBytesRef(value));
    } else {
        Query termQuery = mapper.termQuery(value, context);
        term = MappedFieldType.extractTerm(termQuery);
    }
    return new SpanTermQuery(term);
}
```

In the newer version (ref 6b2cc599cef9c3e075add187cf4b76e1c9977dd0), the method is changed to:
```java
@Override
protected SpanQuery doToQuery(SearchExecutionContext context) throws IOException {
    MappedFieldType mapper = context.getFieldType(fieldName);
    Term term;
    if (mapper == null) {
        return Queries.newMatchNoDocsQuery("Unmapped field [" + fieldName + "]");
    }
    if (mapper.getTextSearchInfo().hasPositions() == false) {
        throw new IllegalArgumentException(
            "Span term query requires position data, but field " + fieldName + " was indexed without position data"
        );
    }
    Query termQuery = mapper.termQuery(value, context);
    List<Term> termsList = new ArrayList<>();
    termQuery.visit(new QueryVisitor() {
        @Override
        public QueryVisitor getSubVisitor(BooleanClause.Occur occur, Query parent) {
            if (occur == BooleanClause.Occur.MUST || occur == BooleanClause.Occur.FILTER) {
                return this;
            }
            return EMPTY_VISITOR;
        }

        @Override
        public void consumeTerms(Query query, Term... terms) {
            termsList.addAll(Arrays.asList(terms));
        }
    });
    if (termsList.size() != 1) {
        throw new IllegalArgumentException("Cannot extract a term from a query of type " + termQuery.getClass() + ": " + termQuery);
    }
    term = termsList.get(0);
    return new SpanTermQuery(term);
}
```

The key change is that when `mapper == null`, the new version returns `Queries.newMatchNoDocsQuery` instead of creating a `SpanTermQuery` with a term on the unmapped field. Also, the new version adds checks on position data and extracts terms differently.

The older version does not have these extra checks or the `MatchNoDocsQuery` return for unmapped fields.

